{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651823","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651823"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:28:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:28:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18495"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18495","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18495"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.14,0.69,0.11,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11224"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114366"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11224","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11224"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18495"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96367"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6638"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26047"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26271"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26272"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27278"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114366","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114366"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe heart receives its blood supply through the coronary arteries, which arise from the ascending aorta immediately superior to the aortic valve. One of these vessels is the anterior interventricular artery (also known as the left anterior descending artery).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the course of this artery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ascends towards the superior vena cava","Courses between the left atrium and left ventricle","Descends in the anterior interventricular sulcus","Runs in the coronary sulcus around the right border of the heart","Travels along the inferior border of the heart"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior interventricular artery\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003E(AIV)\u003C/strong\u003E also known as the left anterior descending artery (LAD) (Image) is a branch of the left coronary artery that descends in the anterior interventricular sulcus. It supplies the anterior two-thirds of the interventricular septum and adjacent ventricular walls.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe course described as \u003Cstrong\u003Erunning in the coronary sulcus around the right border of the heart\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of the right coronary artery, while the path \u003Cstrong\u003Ebetween the left atrium and left ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E describes the circumflex branch of the left coronary artery. No major coronary vessel \u003Cstrong\u003Eascends towards the superior vena cava\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Etravels along the inferior border of the heart\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the course of coronary arteries is essential for interpreting cardiac pathology and planning interventional procedures (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The right coronary artery supplies the right atrium, right ventricle, sinoatrial node, and posterior interventricular septum.","The left coronary artery divides into anterior interventricular and circumflex branches.","The anterior interventricular artery supplies the anterior two-thirds of the interventricular septum."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u0022Total occlusion of Left Anterior descendent artery (LAD)\u0022 by 6129bm is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Total_occlusion_of_Left_Anterior_descendent_artery_(LAD).jpg\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96367"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18495"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21398"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21398"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/kb5p5HIOz23iaUKCUz9L6KuVAUiCax.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/kb5p5HIOz23iaUKCUz9L6KuVAUiCax.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":640}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96367"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T21:13:22+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T21:13:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11224"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114366"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"em